  m_text: Brushed DC servo motors are electromechanical systems that combine traditional
    brushed DC motor technology with precision control capabilities. These motors
    operate as a closed-loop system where a controller uses feedback from an encoder
    to adjust the position and speed of the rotor, which receives current through
    a physical brush and commutator mechanism.
