  m_text: The DC motor is one of the fundamental components of electromechanical
    systems that convert electrical energy into mechanical energy. The operating
    principle of these devices is based on the generation of torque by the magnetic
    force (Lorentz Force) exerted on a conductor when an electric current is passed
    through it while situated within a magnetic field.
