  m_text: Servo motors are closed-loop systems that provide high-precision control
    of angular or linear position, velocity, and acceleration. Unlike a basic DC
    motor, a servo motor does not merely rotate; it continuously monitors the difference
    between the commanded signal sent to it and its actual position to nullify the
    error.
